data.meta_description: Probably the oldest and least successful singer songwriter on show this year. John writes songs exploring “life’s disappointments, bittersweet observations of the human condition, whilst at times employing humour & irony to soften the pain.”He will not sing about train tracks, lost brumbies, or Bluey the dog etc.But try him out, it might be ‘Your … John Wright Read More »
data.text: Tamworth Regional Council acknowledges the Gamilaroi/Kamilaroi people, who are the Traditional Custodians of this land. We would like to pay respect to Elders past and present, and extend that respect to other Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples living in and visiting our region.
